parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The random dimming or complete failure of headlights can significantly reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at night.
symptoms: Headlights randomly dim or turn off
especially when merging onto highways or driving at night.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause a range of issues, including poor acceleration, hesitation, and jolting, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle struggles to stay running in hot weather with the air conditioning on
low voltage codes
toxic smell from the vents
poor acceleration
hesitation
and jolting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents, and can also prevent the driver from accessing important vehicle settings.
symptoms: Center vehicle display intermittent issues
unresponsive display
backup camera turns on while driving forward
failure to connect or respond to phone plugged in USB-C
static in music streamed using USB-C
distorted maps
and inability to use certain features.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to be difficult to control, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when stopping suddenly or on inclines.
symptoms: Squeaking
squealing
and screeching brakes
brake pedal feels and sounds like it has a faulty spring
pedal gets stuck when switching from gas to brake
brake pedal bounces back with a spring feel and noise
difficulty controlling the brake at low speeds
brake feels like it releases while still depressing the brake on an incline
clunking noise when turning left at low speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering and suspension systems can cause the vehicle to be unstable and difficult to control, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when turning or driving on uneven roads.
symptoms: Steering feels off and unstable
steering wheel vibrates at high speeds
rattling noise heard from the front center/passenger side
clunking noise when turning left at low speeds
screw fell out of the vehicle after being serviced.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electronic Stability Control (ESC) and Power Steering System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ESC and power steering systems can cause the vehicle to be difficult to control, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when turning or driving on uneven roads.
symptoms: Error messages "Service ESC" and "Service Power Steering"
brakes become less responsive
engine feels like it slips while rattling from the front.
